text.tspan: Working Memory Task
In this task you will be asked to remember coloured shapes, and recall the colour of
one shape after a brief delay. The task is a little complicated, so lets see how it works.
Working Memory Task
Before the coloured shapes appear, you will see a random number. Start to repeat this
aloud, saying the number approximately twice a second. Your audio will be recorded
to make sure you are doing this.
Working Memory Task
You will then see a number of coloured shapes, presented at the same time. Try
to remember colour of these shapes, and keep repeating the number.
Working Memory Task
The shapes will briefly disappear, and squares in the same position as the previous
shapes will appear.
One square will have a thicker border than the others. Your task is to remember the
colour of the shape in this location.
Working Memory Task
You will need to use your computer mouse to move to the colour on the colourwheel
that most closely matches the colour you remember. Select the colour by left-clicking the
computer mouse while hovering over the colour wheel.
Please try to report the colour as accurately as you can.
Working Memory Task
Once you have selected the colour you remember, you will be shown the correct
answer on the colour wheel. After this, a new trial will begin.
If you have any questions about the experiment, please ask an experimenter now.
Working Memory Task
The task will change slightly now.
Working Memory Task
However, you will be asked to remember the colour of a specific shape that will appear
in the middle of the screen.
Working Memory Task
You will still be asked to repeat a number out loud, and be shown a number of coloured
shapes that you need to try to remember.
Working Memory Task
The rest of the trial will then be the same.
If you have any questions about the experiment, please ask an experimenter now.
